Values refer to the same supplier when they are the same operating business or public trading brand, including ordinary suffix, punctuation, capitalization, branch-location, and corporate-form variants such as Pty Ltd / Limited / Co. / Australia.

Collapse branch pages and regional outlet labels under the supplier brand when the page is clearly part of the same public supplier identity. Keep separate businesses or brands distinct when they market under different supplier names, belong to different corporate families, or the available names are too generic to infer sameness confidently.
